content:
In CRM Analytics, create a column in a Data Prep recipe that displays values based on a formula calculation. The calculation can include input from other fields in the same row or across rows.

To create a formula for the calculated column, select the Formula button () in the Transform toolbar and select Custom Formula.

Enter formulas in EA-SQL format. Functions are listed by category: Window Functions, String Functions, Numeric Functions, Date/Time Functions, and Additional Functions.

Identify each column in the formula by its API name or select it from the Columns tab.

In Output Type, select whether the calculated column's data is text, numeric, date, or datetime.

Based on the output type, you can set attributes such as Precision, Scale, Length, Date Format, and Default Value.

You can also change the label of the calculated column.

The calculated column appears in the recipe preview. You can bucket a formula column or reference it in later formulas defined in the recipe.

Common functions have their own buttons in the Transform toolbar that automatically fill in the formula with the column and predefined syntax.

Date Functions for Formulas
Numeric Operators and Functions for Formulas
String Functions for Formulas
Window Functions for Formulas
Multivalue Functions for Formulas
Additional Functions for Formulas

To view the Graph area, click the Collapse button ().
Save the recipe.
title: Formulas in CRM Analytics
